Qian Qichen Meets With Iranian Deputy Foreign Minister
BEIJING , February 27 ( Xinhua ) -- The Chinese government places great importance on developing relations with Iran and is prepared to strengthen friendship and cooperation between the two countries on the basis of the Five Principles of Peaceful Coexistence .
Related actions will benefit the people of the two nations and will help promote peace and stability in the region , according to Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen .
Qian made the remarks during a meeting with visiting Iranian Deputy Foreign Minister Mohsen Aminzadeh here today .
He expressed China 's satisfaction with the steady progress the two sides have witnessed in political and economic cooperation in recent years .
Iran is a major country in the Persian Gulf and plays an important role in maintaining regional peace and stability , Qian said .
Aminzadeh agreed with Qian 's assessment of bilateral relations .
He said Iran attaches great importance to ties with China and sincerely hopes relations between the two countries will continue to develop .
Aminzadeh and his entourage arrived in Beijing on Thursday to participate in political consultations between foreign ministries of the two countries .
Aminzadeh also met with Chinese Vice-Foreign Minister Tian Zengpei to exchange views on bilateral relations , and regional and international issues of common concern .
